Pre-Game Insights: Four Ugandan referees were appointed by the Confederation of African Football (CAF) to officiate the upcoming FIFA World Cup 2026 Qualifiers (preliminary round) group A duel between Djibouti and Ethiopia.
The match will take place at the El Jadida Stadium (Stade El Abdi) in Morocco on Sunday, 9th June 2024.
The center referee is Ali Sabilla Chelengat, who has exhibited great performances over the years, with his last qualifiers handled in October 2023 between Equatorial Guinea and Namibia.
